tmp_model <- file.path(tempdir(),"lenet5.h5")

letâ€™s download the test dataâ€¦ The data in test data in the hdf5 is of shape [10000,28,28]. We need to use the aperm function to appropriate change the ordering of the indices (like a high dimensional transpose).

test_data <- file.path(tempdir(),"test_data.h5")
if( !file.exists(test_data)){
  file_ls<-drive_ls("https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1-vVvQR3WpYUQRjbyYDVbq8lE0erm0pKt")
  tmp_file <- drive_download( as_id("102e3beHZzomz8YeFyJj5HFdrMaD3CnPt"), path =  test_data)
}
## File downloaded:
## â€¢ 'test' <id: 102e3beHZzomz8YeFyJj5HFdrMaD3CnPt>
## Saved locally as:
## â€¢ '/var/folders/05/hylhd4656cj1qt8n_t7cxl0h0p3tf1/T//Rtmp55tyod/test_data.h5'
data_file <- h5file(test_data)

x <- data_file[["X"]][,,]
xx <- aperm(x,c(3,2,1))
dim(xx) <- c(dim(xx),1)
y <- data_file[["y"]][]
data_file$close_all()
image(t(apply(xx[1,,,], 2, rev)) )   

res_score <- lenet5_model %>% predict(xx)
res_class <- lenet5_model %>% predict(xx) %>% max.col(.)-1
res <- lenet5_model %>% evaluate(xx,y)

signif(res_score,2)
